Iavan Pijoos, News24(Supplied by ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Eleven people have been injured after an explosion at a factory in Sasolburg, Free State, paramedics said on Monday.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics arrived at the factory at 08:00, to find it had already been evacuated.One man had sustained moderate injuries while 10 others had sustained minor injuries, according to Meiring.They were transported to the medical centre.Meiring could not confirm the cause of the explosion, or what kind of explosion it was.ER24 standing by in Sasolburg for an apparent explosion at a Factory. Update to follow. @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews @News24_SA pic.twitter.com/Jz9UxKxpAb&mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) May 22, 2017ER24 standing by in Sasolburg for an apparent explosion at a Factory. Update to follow. @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews @News24_SA pic.twitter.com/Jz9UxKxpAb24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.